title: King's College Hospital
description:
An NHS Trust, King's is a large teaching hospital with many specialist services.

The site incorporates Medical School facilities, which, following merger with the medical school at Guy's and St Thomas' Hospitals, are now part of GKT under the auspices of King's College London.

title: The Oval Cricket Ground
description:
Home of Surrey County Cricket Club and England Cricket Club

Test Ground and Surrey County Cricket Club.

The club colours are chocolate brown and silver. The club badge is the Prince of Wales' three feathers. Lord Rosebery obtained the permission to use this symbol from the Prince of Wales, owner of the land on which The Oval stands, in 1915.
